+# 5.0-app-install screenshot: unavailable
+
+The GitHub App required by Unit 5 (Out-of-Repo Prereq #1) was created and
+installed on `liatrio/gratibot` by a GitHub org admin. The operator running
+this spec did not have access to screenshot the App installation page, so
+`5.0-app-install.png` is not available in this proofs directory.
+
+**Substitute evidence:** the post-merge release run artifact
+`5.0-release-run.txt` (Task 7.6) demonstrates the App was created and
+installed with sufficient permissions — `actions/create-github-app-token`
+successfully mints a token and `semantic-release` successfully publishes a
+GitHub Release using it, which exercises the `contents: write`, `issues: write`,
+and `pull-requests: write` permissions end-to-end. A failing token mint
+(wrong App ID, missing key) or a failing release step (insufficient
+permissions) would break the job; a green run is positive proof that the
+App is installed with at least the required permissions.
+
+**Confirmation recorded at handoff:** the user confirmed Task 5.1 was
+completed by an org admin on 2026-04-16.
+
+If a screenshot is required for the validation phase, an org admin can
+capture one from the installation page at
+`https://github.com/organizations/liatrio/settings/installations` and add it
+to this directory as `5.0-app-install.png`.
